    "Fair and Warmer The Maiwme Be mdicht Entered as Second Class Matter at Post Office at Waterbury Conn Under the Act of March 3 1879 Final Edition ESTABLISHED 1881 VOL LXIV NO 230 THE WATERBURY DEMOCRAT WATERBURY CONN SATURDAY SEPTEMBER 28 1946 TEN PAGES PRICE 4 CENTS Slavs Defeated on French Line Judgment Draws Near For Apostles of Nazism Nuernberg Sept 28UPThe War Crimes Tribunal announced today that jurisdiction over the 22 Nazi leaders whose fate will be announced Monday and Tuesday will be handed over to a fourpower committee of generals when judgment is handed down The four generals have arrived from Berlin as repre sentatives of the Allied Control Council for Germany The uouncu win conduct anjr executions ordered by the Tribunal BrigGen Roy V Rickard is the American representative on the generals committee Others are Brig Paton Walsh of Britain Gen eral Molkov Russia and General Morel Prance Fate of Condemned Men Unknown What will happen to Nazis receiv ing the death sentence was still secret The Allied Counc has de cided that the executions must be private with newspapermen and public witnesses barred It was understood executions would occur on the 15th day after sentence is"
